Every single talent that's worth a shit will be virtually retired within 10 years. The content bubble will burst before that as well, which is why Vince is trying to sell to the most content-starved content provider. The only reason WWE has such a high valuation is because media companies have backed themselves into a content ponzi scheme. They constantly need a flow of new shit to shill to their existing subscriber base or those subscribers will go away. People don't realize just how close the end is for wrestling, let alone the entire media landscape.

There are no young draws in the entire wrestling business. There's nothing to replace the current crop of talent that will be retiring in the next decade. People don't realize that the "new generation" that was supposed to keep the wrestling business alive are almost aged out themselves. Roman Reigns, Seth Rollins, Kevin Owens, Cody Rhodes and Sami Zayn are all in their late 30s. If you think these guys were dimeless fucks, just wait until you see how badly their juniors will fare comparatively. We already have an idea of what the 20-something talents offer in terms of drawing an audience with AEW's roster.

Vince knows the business is running on fumes. It's in the beginnings of a death spiral into roller derby levels of cultural irrelevance. Selling WWE right now will be the best and biggest carny act that he ever executed. Potential buyers would benefit by letting the wrestling business die its inevitable death before wasting billions on buying its largest entity.

The main event garnered a 2.67 cable rating (2.55 for the first half of the bout), which Meltzer says is by far, the lowest-rated main event on Raw in 2011 and possibly the lowest since 1997 for a non-holiday show in its regular time slot.

Honestly yeah. It is an absolute game changer. I am getting framerate and clarity that would only be possible at 360 with 3mb.
There have been some weird errors popping up when I have been making webms for /pw/ since the change. The biggest one is the "Error: Embedded Image" which I think is related to webm being an offshot of the Matroska file format. The mkv file format is a container so every element of it is, techinically speaking, embeded. I have shot off a few emails to the admins, but it doesn't seem like they have been working on it.

The embedded image error goes back to 2006 when the glowniggers started hiding CP inside of png files and then leaked how to do so on /b/. It was a massive issue for about a year or two before they began filtering for embedded files. I understand Hebrewjewki Niggersaki wanting to keep that up, but they will need to test to find a way to filter for legitimate webm before some wise guy figures out a way to embed codices other than VP8/Orbis or VP9/Opus in there. Worst case scenario someone will figure out a way to embed a second video track or image files in the gif or png format.

Steiner has attacked Eric Bischoff, calling him an "idiot" among other things, particularly for praising Ric Flair at a TV production meeting as a "two time HOF'er". OK, even if you think Bischoff is a bit of a hypocrite RE: Flair given their well known issues in the past, has Steiner ever publicly acknowledged the fact that EZ E gave him the biggest push and contract extension he ever had during his "Big Poppa Pump" heyday with the NWO in the late 90s ? Breaking up the Steiner Brothers tag team, having Scott turn heel, creating the whole "Poppa Pump" persona, joining the NWO, who was behind all that, wasnt it Bischoff ? Certainly the one career huge contract he got in 1998 was spearheaded by Bischoff. Has Steiner ever publicly acknowledged this?

Flair on the other hand had almost no stroke with Bischoff during that time so he certainly wasnt holding him back. Steiner got his break in the industry thanks to Flair, who pitched him hard to WCW management as a favor to Rick Steiner. It seems to me these guys did far more to make his career than they ever did to hurt it. If it weren't for guys like Flair, brother Rick, Bischoff, Hogan, Vince, HHH, HBK and Stephanie, Scott wouldn't even have an overall sketchy wrestling career filled with attitude questions. Steiner goes off on Triple H, HBK, & Vince McMahon almost as often as he does on Flair & Hogan. Never any mention of the fact that Vince hired him TWICE to work for him (also, if the first stint didnt go as well as Steiner would have liked whose fault was that, Flair, Hogan, HHH, Bischoff, none of them were involved with WWE during that time, hardly if at all). Steiner was pushed into the main events and put over heavily on WWE TV when he returned for is last stint almost immediately.

I get that maybe he thinks his career should have been bigger and better appreciated than it was, though he certainly had a decent to good career by any measure.
